Method Detail

getFileTemplate

public static java.io.InputStream getFileTemplate(IFile file,
                                                  java.lang.String templateFile)
Initializes file contents with a template. The contents of the template are loaded, and then the following fields are filled in:

${file} - The name of the file, including extension

${name} - The name of the file, minus the extension.

${filePath} - The full path of the file.

${template} - The name of the template that is being loaded from.

${parentDir} - The name of the directory the file is in.

${date} - The current date and time.

${project} - The project this file belongs to.

${createdComment} - A Soar comment telling the name of the file and when it was created.

Parameters:
file - The file to be initialized.
templateFile - The name of the template file.
Returns:
A Stream containing the contents to be placed in the file.

markResource

Parameters:

isFolderFile

public static boolean isFolderFile(IResource res)
Determines if this is the soar file that represents the folder, ie: the file that would be opened if we double-clicked the folder from Visual Soar's navigator. Basically, it sees if the resource's name is the same as that of its parent folder. My apologies to everyone for not coming up with a better name.

Parameters:
res - The resource to check
Returns:
true if it represents the folder, false if not.

folderify

public static IContainer folderify(IResource res,
                                   IProgressMonitor monitor)
Prepares a Soar resource for having a[n] {suboperator|file|impasse} added to it. If the resource is a file not inside a folder of the same name, it creates that folder, moves this file there, creates a datamap, etc. The value returned is the folder in which the new file should be placed.

Parameters:
res - The resources to folderify.
monitor - A progress monitor.
Returns:
The folder in which to place the new file.

getAvailableName

public static java.lang.String getAvailableName(IResource res,
                                                java.lang.String nameSuggestion)
Finds an available filename to go in whatever folder this resource will be in once we folderify it. The file's name is based off of nameSuggestion, with a number added to make it unique, as well as a .soar extension.

Parameters:
res - The resource we will be adding to.
nameSuggestion - A suggestion for the file name.
Returns:
A unique file name.
